caption:
COTTAGE CHEESE ORZO PASTINA!! Been a second since I’ve hit up Big Cottage so I’m bringing back this 15 minute recipe since my true passion in life is eating all my meals with a spoon!!!

CC Orzo Pastina 
1 cup full fat cottage cheese
1 cup finely grated parm
2 large eggs
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper 
1 pound dried orzo
4 cups vegetable or chicken stock

In a mini food processor or blend, combine the cottage cheese, parm, eggs, and a heavy pinch each of salt and pepper and purée until very smooth. 

In a medium pot, combine the orzo and stock over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring often, until all the liquid is absorbed and the pasta is al dente, 12-15 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the cottage cheese mixture. Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt and pepper, then serve. 

#pasta #cottagecheese #orzo

caption:
I can never get enough of this Baked Jamaican Pineapple Jerk Chicken. It’s the real deal!  Don’t believe me——-ask somebody! ✌

YOUR GROCERY LIST:

Chicken. You can use a mixture of thighs, wings, and drumsticks, just remove the skin first. See recipe for other meats that work really well with jerk also!
Jerk seasoning. I like two layers of seasoning for this dish. You can purchase a store-bought version or create a homemade blend using a handful of herbs + seasonings.
Thyme. I recommend fresh, but if you only have dried, use a half teaspoon.
Scotch bonnet. If you don’t like spice, use less of the peppers. You can also sub with habanero peppers.
Vinegar. This adds acidity to the jerk seasoning paste. You can substitute with apple cider vinegar, if preferred.
Water. You can use filtered water or add additional flavor with chicken stock. I like to use organic chicken stock, you can also use veggie stock if preferred.
Brown sugar. This adds a hint of sweetness to balance the heat. I like to use organic brown sugar, however, you can substitute with honey or maple syrup.
Pimento seeds. Also known as allspice, which is a Jamaican pepper that is basically a dried unripe fruit of the Pimenta tree. You can substitute with ground cayenne pepper (about ½ tsp), if you don’t have these seeds on hand.
Carrots. I love adding carrots. You can peel + chop and use them raw or roast them for added flavor.
Red onion. Substitute with yellow or white.
Garlic + ginger. I prefer fresh, but you could substitute with 1 teaspoon garlic powder and ½ teaspoon ground ginger in a pinch.
Soy sauce. I like to add soy sauce for additional saltiness and umami flavor, but you can omit this or substitute with tamari, Worcestershire, etc.
Pineapple chunks. I like to purchase canned organic pineapple when convenient, however, you can slice an actual pineapple into chunks.
————————————————————-

#orchidsandsweettea #pineapple #jerkchicken #jerk #bakedchicken #cooking

scotch bonnet. if you don’t like spice, use less of the peppers. you can also sub with habanero peppers.
vinegar. this adds acidity to the jerk seasoning paste. you can substitute with apple cider vinegar, if preferred.
water. you can use filtered water or add additional flavor with chicken stock. i like to use organic chicken stock, you can also use veggie stock if preferred.
brown sugar. this adds a hint of sweetness to balance the heat. i like to use organic brown sugar, however, you can substitute with honey or maple syrup.
pimento seeds. also known as allspice, which is a jamaican pepper that is basically a dried unripe fruit of the pimenta tree. you can substitute with ground cayenne pepper (about ½ tsp), if you don’t have these seeds on hand.
carrots. i love adding carrots. you can peel + chop and use them raw or roast them for added flavor.
red onion. substitute with yellow or white.
garlic + ginger. i prefer fresh, but you could substitute with 1 teaspoon garlic powder and ½ teaspoon ground ginger in a pinch.
soy sauce. i like to add soy sauce for additional saltiness and umami flavor, but you can omit this or substitute with tamari, worcestershire, etc.
pineapple chunks. i like to purchase canned organic pineapple when convenient, however, you can slice an actual pineapple into chunks.
————————————————————-

caption:
Save this almond milk hack and use it for Passover and always‼️

Once you try it, you’ll never go back to using cheesecloths.  It took literally 30 seconds to make, plus it doesn’t have any of the sugar, gums+ preservatives many store bought brands have 

✨ Blend 1 heaping tbsp (abt 1.5 tbsp) natural almond butter with 3 c water (add a little more if you like it thinner), add a date for sweeter or a splash of vanilla to add flavor and blend until smooth.  

Store in the fridge for 3-4 days and use as you would any almond milk. 

How cool is that?! Tap the ❤️ if you think so too!

(I used my @ninjakitchen Foodi to blend. It’s linked on my amazon page- through my link in bio) 
.
.
.
.

caption:
الارز مع اللحم والكستناء ؛ 
المكونات ؛ 
كوبين من حبات الكستناء المقشرة مسبقا 
نصف كوب كستناء مفروم 
كوبين ونصف ارز بسمتي او ٣ اكواب ارز صنوايت 
نصف كيلو لحم غنم مفروم 
كيلو من لحم الموزات او كتف مقطع مع العظام 
بصلة مفرومة 
مكسرات محمصة للتقديم 
بهارات سلق اللحم ( ورق غار - ٥ حبات هيل- فلفل اسود حب - كبش قرنفل حب - بصلة - عودين قرفة - ) 
بهارات طبخ الارز ؛ ملح - ملعقة كبيرة بهارات مشكلة او بهار عادي - فلفل اسود - نصف م ص قرفة - رشة جوزة الطيب - ن م ص كمون - رشة كاري . 
سمن - زيت حسب الرغبة . 
مرق اللحم لطبخ الارز 
الطريقة ؛ 
يجب تحضير الكستناء مسبقا بتقطيعها وشويها وتقشيرها

TranslatedText:
Rice with meat and chestnuts; 
the components ; 
Two cups of pre-peeled chestnuts 
Half a cup of chopped chestnuts 
Two and a half cups of basmati rice or 3 cups of Sunwhite rice 
Half a kilo of minced lamb 
A kilo of banana meat or shoulder cut with bones 
Chopped onion 
Roasted nuts for serving 
Meat boiling spices (bay leaves - 5 cardamom pods - black pepper - 1 clove - onion - 2 cinnamon sticks -) 
Rice cooking spices; Salt - a tablespoon of mixed spices or regular spices - black pepper - half a teaspoon of cinnamon - a pinch of nutmeg - a pinch of cumin - a pinch of curry. 
Ghee - oil as desired. 
Meat broth for cooking rice 
method; 
Chestnuts must be prepared in advance by cutting, roasting and peeling them 
Its method and method for sorting it are already present on the page 
The first step is to boil the chopped meat of bananas or shoulder in water with the correct flavorings and spices mentioned, while removing all the excrement from the surface of the broth. Leave it for two hours until done. Filter the broth and leave it aside.
Soak basmati rice for an hour or soak the sundaes for only half an hour. Then wash and filter. And the sequel is in the video, made with love.ae #recipe #recipeoftheday #food #foodporn #foodphotography #foodblogger #foodstagram #foofighterslive #explore #explorepage #exploremore #trend #trendy #delicious #tasty #cooking

לחיות במדינת ישראל זה מירוץ יומי .
תמיד היה כאן ככה. 
בשנים האחרונות המירוץ הגביר קצב ונהיה מאוד מהיר מבלי שאפשר לעצור רגע לנשום. 
הרבה אנשים בורחים מהמירוץ לקפיצה קטנה מעבר לים זאת אופציה טובה אבל אפשר גם אחרת. 

אפשר ליצור אתנחתא קטנה מהמירוץ ופשוט להנות מאסטטיקה משובחת ,אוכל טוב ,חברה נעימה ואלכוהול משובח. 

זה אפשרי וזה תלוי רק בהחלטה שלנו .

TranslatedText:
Living in the State of Israel is a daily race.
It's always been like this here. 
In recent years the race has increased its pace and has become very fast without being able to stop for a moment to breathe. 
Many people run away from the race for a small jump overseas, this is a good option, but it is also possible otherwise. 

You can create a small retreat from the race and simply enjoy fine aesthetics, good food, pleasant company and fine alcohol. 

It is possible and it depends only on our decision.

caption:
South Africa's opening stratement on the Israeli Genocide at the ICJ. We know that the ICJ was never meant to hear the cases of the oppressed peoples. The British, US and European imperialists have never been dragged before this court for their crimes, and they have done everything to avoid the exposure of their agent, Israel.
One of two things: either Israel will be convicted of genocide and will stand even more exposed ok in the eyes of the world; or the imperialist court will "absolve" Israel, and will be finished as an institution in the eyes of the world. In either case, Imperialism, the real agents of humanity's pain and misery, will be fuether harmed, and the people of all countries will take another step toward freedom. Don't let up the struggle for a moment. The suffering of the Palestinian people, and the working and toiling nasses of all countries, must end! Long live Palestime! Long Live Gaza!
Notes: author of Palestine on a Plate

caption:
“This is not war. This is slaughter.”

US congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez on Tuesday criticised a proposal for the US to send an additional $17.6 billion in aid to Israel, which was later rejected. Ocasio-Cortez described Israel’s assault on Gaza as “ineffective” and said they were “nowhere close to their stated objective of destroying Hamas”.

In recent months the congresswoman has been criticised by some of her constituents for not being vocal enough about the situation in Gaza and continuing to back US President Joe Biden’s bid for the 2024 presidential election despite his support for Israel.

caption:
I think of Ahmad Manasra almost everyday especially during prayer, I remember the horrifying scene of when he was a laying on the concrete after being run over by a settler’s car bleeding on the street with his legs contorted beneath him all while illegal settlers were tormenting him. He was only 13 years old.

My heart still bleeds for him and the brutal torture he has been experiencing for many years now. His mental health has declined immensely. His childhood stolen by the occupier. #freeahmadmanasra via @suzytamimi 

Caption below and video @ahmad_elite
Ahmad Manasra, along side thousands of Palestinians who are in jail for no reason and no just process. Most of the time, these kids are abducted in the middle of the night from their beds by IDF soldiers, with no hope of seeing their family again. Did you know Palestinians have to go through a Military court system? With a 99% conviction rate? I CALL THESE HOSTAGES and Israel has been taking them for decades #freepalestine #gazaunderattack #westbank
